citation: Proclamation under the Child Care Act 2001 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Child Care Act 2001

I, the Administrator in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2(2) of the Child Care Act 2001 fix 1 September 2003 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, other than Part 1 , Division 4 of Part 8 and sections 71 , 72 , 73 , 74 , 75 and 76 , commence.

19 May 2003

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Administrator

By His Excellency's Command,

PAULA WRIEDT

Minister for Education

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 28 May 2003

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Education.
